<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="1005" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1059,855,907]" pageId="46" pageNumber="1005">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name, 
<emphasis box="[537,631,855,876]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="1005">cassidilis</emphasis>
, is a Latin noun with a meaning of &quot;small bag&quot;; with reference to the small paralateral saccular structures on sternites II-IV.
</paragraph>
